    <section id="postingbody">
        <div class="print-information print-qrcode-container">
            <p class="print-qrcode-label">QR Code Link to This Post</p>
            <div class="print-qrcode" data-location="http://newyork.craigslist.org/mnh/fbh/6046602254.html"></div>
        </div>
Are you excited at the prospect of being part of a brand new concept with a highly motivated, driven and diverse team? If so, Fatbird Southern Kitchen &amp; Bar is looking to hire talented Restaurant Managers for its FIRST location at 44th 9th Ave, we'd love to hear from you!<br>
<br>
We offer:<br>
<br>
*Strong career advancement opportunities within the New York area, nationally, and abroad.<br>
<br>
*Strong compensation package for qualified individuals.<br>
<br>
<br>
As a Fatbird Restaurant Manager you would:<br>
<br>
*Lead a team to create a high quality personalized experience, in line with the Fatbird southern-hospitality brand.  <br>
<br>
*Direct and coach team members to provide superior service and guest satisfaction.<br>
<br>
*Continuously seek ways to improve our performance, we look for innovative ways to "surprise and delight" with each guest encounter by creating ambience unlike any other, providing an energetic, personable, and diverse service team, while demonstrating an acute attention to detail.<br>
<br>
Guest Service teams will be progressively developed and cross-trained, enabling them to work every station in their areas of expertise, wherever and whenever needed, to create a synergy that is seamless, magical, and financially prudent.<br>
<br>
<br>
Must have:<br>
<br>
*A minimum of 3 years management experience.<br>
<br>
*Ability to multitask in a high volume environment while maintaining service standards, a sense of humor and appearing calm.<br>
<br>
*Impeccable attention to detail, ability to be attentive to guests while also playing a supportive role to front of house staff. <br>
<br>
*Ability to lead a team, establish service standards and positively influence employee behavior.<br>
<br>
*Strong financial and computer skills; experience working with and an understanding of P&amp;L's.<br>
<br>
*Ability to work a flexible schedule when necessary.<br>
<br>
<br>
Fatbird will make a personal commitment to each associate's growth and development, continually challenging and encouraging them to master their craft and become leaders in their field.<br>
<br>
If you meet all of these qualifications and are looking to work in a fast-paced growing establishment, please submit a resume along with a strong cover letter telling us why you'd excel as a Fatbird Restaurant Manager!    </section>

